%20massive%20gap%20in%20values%20between%20Gen%20Z%20and%20hiring%20managers%2C%20according%20to%20a%20new%20study.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EGen%20Z%20prioritizes%20self-care%2C%20while%20employers%20seek%20success-driven%20candidates%2C%20the%20findings%20show.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20friction%20is%20creating%20hiring%20frustrations%2C%20but%20there%20are%20ways%20to%20close%20the%20gap.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EGen%20Z%20and%20hiring%20managers%20are%20at%20odds.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EZoomers'%20core%20values%20in%20life%20and%20work%20don't%20jive%20with%20the%20values%20that%20employers%20desire%20most%20in%20new%20recruits%2C%20research%20shows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20suggests%20there's%20%26quot%3Ba%20fork%20in%20the%20road%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Suzy%20Welch%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20New%20York%20University's%20Stern%20School%20of%20Business%20who%20led%20a%20recent%20study%20behind%20the%20findings.%20%26quot%3BGen%20Z%20has%20a%20set%20of%20values%2C%20and%20hiring%20managers%20are%20looking%20for%20a%20different%20set.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20top%20of%20employers'%20wish%20lists%20are%20job%20applicants%20who%20want%20success%20that%20others%20recognize%2C%20the%20finding%20shows.%20But%20for%20Gen%20Z%2C%20that%20value%20ranks%20at%20No.%2011.%20They%20place%20%26quot%3Beudemonia%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20encompasses%20self-care%2C%20pleasure%2C%20and%20recreation%2C%20at%20No.%201.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20second%20place%20for%20employers%20is%20scope%2C%20or%20the%20desire%20for%20action%20and%20stimulation%2C%20which%20includes%20learning%20and%20travel.%20That's%20followed%20by%20%26quot%3Bwork-centrism%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20seeing%20work%20as%20central%20to%20one's%20decision-making%20and%20behavior.%20Gen%20Z%20ranked%20those%20values%20at%20No.%2010%20and%20No.%209%2C%20and%20gave%20the%20No.%202%20and%20No.%203%20spots%20instead%20to%20voice%2C%20or%20authentic%20individuality%2C%20and%20the%20desire%20to%20have%20a%20life%20or%20career%20that%20involves%20helping%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20overall%20disparity%20Welch%20found%20was%20huge%3A%20Only%202%25%20of%20Zoomers%20align%20with%20the%20values%20employers%20most%20prize.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20findings%20are%20based%20in%20part%20on%20responses%20from%2045%2C000%20US%20participants%20%E2%80%94%20including%20more%20than%207%2C500%20Gen%20Zers%20%E2%80%94%20to%20a%20scientifically%20validated%2C%20behaviorally%20based%20assessment%20tool%20called%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthevaluesbridge.com%2F%3Futm_source%3Dwsj%26utm_medium%3Dorganic%26utm_campaign%3Dvalues_disconnect_sep25%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EValues%20Bridge%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20Welch%20created%20with%20a%20team%20of%20experts.%20It%20ranks%2016%20values%20from%20answers%20to%20100%20behavioral%20questions.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EAlso%20taken%20into%20account%20are%20results%20from%20a%20survey%20of%202%2C100%20US%20hiring%20managers%20over%20the%20age%20of%2040%20with%20at%20least%20five%20direct%20reports%20in%20white-collar%20roles%2C%20such%20as%20banking%20and%20consulting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22370a470c-b53e-4e93-b419-811d9f2eb941%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%2C%20who%20is%20right%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGen%20Z%20has%20entered%20the%20workforce%20amid%20widening%20political%20divides%2C%20mass%20shootings%2C%20and%20pandemic-era%20upheaval.%20Many%20are%20seeing%20their%20parents%20lose%20jobs%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-x-side-hustles-odd-jobs-unemployment-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Estruggle%20financially%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20while%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fimpact-ai-job-market-change-role-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eartificial-intelligence%20boom%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20disrupting%20the%20workplace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhy%20should%20they%20sign%20up%20for%20the%20bargain%20their%20parents%20have%3F%26quot%3B%20said%20Welch%2C%20referring%20to%20what%20she%20often%20hears%20from%20her%20Gen%20Z%20students.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20for%20older%20professionals%2C%20having%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-hustle-culture-toxic-productivity-defined-my-early-career-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bhustle%26quot%3B%20mentality%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20makes%20sense%2C%20because%20their%20values%20link%20%26quot%3Bback%20to%20a%20style%20of%20working%20that%20they've%20seen%20actually%20produce%20results%20in%20a%20competitive%20marketplace%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%20%26quot%3BThey%20think%20these%20are%20the%20values%20that%20are%20going%20to%20allow%20us%20to%20remain%20profitable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223744%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Suzy%20Welch%20smiles%20while%20sitting%20on%20a%20cushion.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68f1085a1c1f80efbec5b463%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225616%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESuzy%20Welch%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20New%20York%20University's%20Stern%20School%20of%20Business%2C%20led%20a%20study%20that%20shows%20a%20values%20gap%20between%20Gen%20Z%20and%20employers.%3Cp%3EBrooks%20Kraft%20LLC%2FCorbis%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWelch%20stressed%20that%20neither%20Gen%20Z%20nor%20their%20older%20counterparts%20are%20inherently%20wrong.%20Values%20are%20choices%2C%20not%20virtues.%20Yet%20both%20groups%20tend%20to%20point%20fingers%20at%20one%20another.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20always%20are%20claiming%20we%20don't%20judge%2C%20and%20then%20we%20judge%2C%20and%20it's%20toxic%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Welch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2279cc3349-4183-448d-b1e4-1ab79a1b8a3d%5C%22%3EHiring%20woes%20for%20all%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20values%20gap%20comes%20at%20a%20time%20when%20Gen%20Z%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-unemployed-dream-jobs-hiring-college-degree-graduation-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Estruggling%20to%20find%20work%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20part%20because%20there%20are%20more%20job%20seekers%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstates-unemployment-claims-rising-most-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eopen%20positions%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20June%2C%20the%20unemployment%20rate%20for%20recent%20college%20graduates%20was%204.8%25%2C%20compared%20with%204%25%20for%20all%20workers%2C%20according%20to%20the%20latest%20figures%20available%20from%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20New%20York.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20impediment%20for%20Gen%20Z%20is%20that%20many%20workers%20are%20staying%20put%E2%80%94%20a%20phenomenon%20some%20call%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworkers-job-hugging-hopping-labor-market-growth-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejob%20hugging%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20The%20Labor%20Department's%20most%20recent%20data%20show%20the%20share%20of%20workers%20voluntarily%20leaving%20their%20jobs%20was%20just%201.9%25%20in%20August.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20values%20gap%20may%20be%20making%20it%20difficult%20for%20hiring%20managers%20to%20fill%20junior%20roles%20with%20the%20kind%20of%20talent%20they%20covet%20most.%20Welch%20and%20other%20workplace%20researchers%20say%20a%20lack%20of%20candid%20communication%20between%20the%20two%20cohorts%20may%20be%20at%20least%20partly%20to%20blame.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20Jeff%20LeBlanc%2C%20a%20management%20lecturer%20at%20Bentley%20University%20in%20Waltham%2C%20Massachusetts%2C%20said%20a%20former%20Gen%20Z%20student%20of%20his%20expected%20a%20promotion%20after%20three%20months%20on%20the%20job.%20The%20problem%20wasn't%20entitlement%2C%20LeBlanc%20said%2C%20but%20that%20the%20student's%20manager%20had%20never%20explained%20the%20company's%20promotion%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20key%20is%20clarity%20and%20really%20being%20upfront%20in%20terms%20of%20what%20the%20job%20is%20going%20to%20look%20like%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20older%20workers%20might%20assume%20that%20Gen%20Z%20highly%20values%20fame%2C%20given%20the%20prominence%20of%20young%20social-media%20personalities.%20But%20Welch's%20study%20shows%20that%20Gen%20Z%20ranks%20fame%2C%20which%20it%20refers%20to%20as%20%26quot%3Bluminance%2C%26quot%3B%20dead%20last%20at%20No.%2016.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEmployers%20fear%20that%20Gen%20Z%20wants%20a%20spotlight%2C%20but%20they%20don't%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Welch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c98269c2-97d1-4ec6-9f92-ffa121e70755%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBridging%20the%20gap%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Gen%20Z%2C%20bridging%20the%20gap%20with%20older%20generations%20starts%20with%20reframing%20the%20interview%2C%20said%20Jeremy%20Schifeling%2C%20an%20early-stage%20career%20advisor.%20Rather%20than%20emphasizing%20personal%20fulfillment%2C%20young%20job%20seekers%20should%20highlight%20how%20they%20can%20contribute%20to%20an%20employer's%20goals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20have%20to%20lie%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20just%20have%20to%20think%20about%20more%20than%20just%20yourself.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20isn't%20a%20trade-off%2C%20Schifeling%20added.%20%26quot%3BYou'll%20have%20a%20chance%20to%20have%20work-life%20balance%20and%20set%20your%20own%20hours%20and%20all%20that%20down%20the%20road%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20the%20way%20you%20get%20to%20that%20golden%20ticket%20is%20by%20starting%20with%20an%20orientation%20around%20others%2C%20not%20just%20the%20self.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20their%20part%2C%20experienced%20hiring%20managers%20can%20continue%20to%20look%20for%20that%20tiny%20fraction%20of%20Gen%20Zers%20whose%20values%20align%20with%20theirs.%20Welch%20said%20the%20head%20of%20human%20resources%20for%20an%20investment%20bank%20told%20h