0feel%20less%20urgency%20to%20stretch%20compensation%20to%20keep%20you%20because%20they%20know%20strong%20replacements%20are%20ready%20and%20willing.%20Second%2C%20if%20you%20do%20decide%20to%20leave%2C%20they%20may%20see%20it%20as%20a%20cost-saving%20opportunity%20to%20eliminate%20your%20role%20or%20put%20someone%20less%20expensive%20in%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20doesn't%20mean%20raises%20are%20off%20the%20table.%20It%20means%20you%20need%20to%20be%20thoughtful%20and%20self-aware%20about%20how%20you%20ask.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2229da6991-a9bc-419e-abc9-4b9e5152c91c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMake%20sure%20you%20know%20your%20pay%20band%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20organizations%20have%20pre-determined%20compensation%20ranges%20for%20each%20employee%20level.%20Employees%20who%20hold%20a%20certain%20title%20need%20to%20be%20compensated%20somewhere%20within%20the%20range%2C%20or%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-pay-guidelines-new-hire-offers-exception-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epay%20band%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20for%20their%20title.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAsk%20HR%20or%20your%20manager%20where%20you%20fall%20within%20the%20pay%20range%20for%20your%20role.%20Even%20if%20that%20person%20won't%20share%20specifics%2C%20you're%20entitled%20to%20know%20whether%20there's%20room%20for%20a%20raise%2C%20assuming%20you%20hit%20certain%20objectives%20and%20the%20company%20is%20in%20a%20position%20to%20provide%20salary%20increases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20already%20at%20the%20top%20of%20the%20range%2C%20focus%20on%20positioning%20yourself%20for%20the%20next%20level%20instead%20of%20pushing%20for%20more%20in%20the%20current%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228c795de7-212b-406a-b39b-cbd26c3f0b76%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EDon't%20treat%20base%20salary%20as%20the%20only%20leverage%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20seen%20employees%20become%20demoralized%20when%20their%20company%20denies%20a%20base%20salary%20increase%2C%20but%20they're%20missing%20out%20on%20other%20ways%20to%20increase%20their%20compensation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20one%20retailer%2C%20an%20employee%20on%20my%20team%20asked%20for%20a%20raise%20during%20a%20year%20when%20the%20budget%20was%20tight.%20We%20couldn't%20adjust%20her%20salary%2C%20but%20I%20was%20able%20to%20secure%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-employee-pay-incentivize-higher-performance-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eperformance%20bonus%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20a%20retention%20incentive%20in%20the%20form%20of%20company%20stock.%20She%20ended%20up%20doing%20better%20financially%20over%20a%20three-year%20period%20than%20she%20would've%20done%20with%20the%20raise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAsk%20about%20retention%20bonuses%2C%20project-based%20incentives%2C%20stock%20grants%2C%20or%20some%20kind%20of%20continuing%20education.%20Companies%20often%20have%20more%20flexibility%20outside%20base%20salary%20because%20they're%20less%20subject%20to%20pay%20bands%20and%20aren't%20increasing%20the%20baseline%20that%20you'll%20be%20paid%20each%20year%20going%20forward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22be7b55a4-a201-4749-ac26-9f47c9e027c1%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EConsider%20the%20timing%20of%20your%20ask%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftop-5-reasons-employees-denied-raises-promotions-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAs%20I've%20said%20before%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20is%20one%20of%20the%20top%20mistakes%20I've%20seen%20people%20make%20in%20any%20market%2C%20and%20it%20applies%20even%20more%20so%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20once%20had%20a%20high%20performer%20ask%20for%20a%20raise%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20a%20quarter%20when%20the%20business%20had%20just%20missed%20its%20numbers.%20Her%20case%20was%20good%2C%20but%20the%20timing%20made%20her%20seem%20oblivious%20to%20the%20reality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20your%20boss%20is%20overwhelmed%2C%20the%20company%20is%20in%20crisis%2C%20or%20you've%20just%20missed%20a%20milestone%2C%20hold%20off.%20Wait%20until%20you've%20delivered%20a%20win%2C%20the%20business%20has%20breathing%20room%2C%20and%20decision-makers%20are%20in%20a%20better%20mindset%20to%20support%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222b6291fc-bec4-4285-a470-c885460bdd87%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EUse%20salary%20transparency%20data%20wisely%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20had%20employees%20overload%20my%20email%20inbox%20with%20screenshots%20from%20salary%20websites%2C%20attempting%20to%20make%20a%20case%20that%20they%20were%20underpaid.%20These%20sites%20are%20full%20of%20self-reported%20data%20that's%20rarely%20specific%20enough%20to%20the%20company%2C%20industry%2C%20scope%20of%20role%2C%20and%20geography%20at%20hand.%20Managers%20and%20HR%20leaders%20don't%20see%20them%20as%20credible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20use%20specific%2C%20verified%20data%20that's%20relevant%20to%20your%20exact%20situation%2C%20including%20anecdotes%20you%20can%20get%20from%20peers%20in%20your%20company%20and%20industry.%20That%20shows%20you've%20done%20your%20homework%20and%20positions%20you%20as%20a%20professional%2C%20not%20a%20complainer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20think%20of%20it%20as%20a%20starting%20point%20for%20asking%20HR%20whether%20they're%20open%20to%20conducting%20a%20compensation%20assessment%20to%20determine%20whether%20you're%20eligible%20for%20a%20pay%20adjustment%20instead%20of%20acting%20like%20you're%20entitled%20to%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2225e44749-d65e-49e0-a576-26fc070637e0%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHere's%20the%20best%20advice%20I%20give%20my%20coaching%20clients%3A%20Make%20yourself%20indispensable%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20doesn't%20always%20mean%20working%20longer%20hours%20(although%2C%20let's%20be%20honest%2C%20sometimes%20it%20does).%20It%20means%20doing%20excellent%20work%20on%20projects%20that%20matter%20most%20to%20the%20company%20%E2%80%94%20and%20making%20sure%